"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s31",
"title":{
"__html":"Cirrhosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"f21b78",
"children":[
"Cirrhosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s31_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b169c3",
"children":[
"Patients with ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"complications of cirrhosis"
]
},
" (hepatic encephalopathy, variceal hemorrhage, ascites, spontaneous bacterial peritonitis, hepatorenal syndrome, jaundice, or ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hepatocellular carcinoma",
"children":[
"HCC"
]
},
") have decompensated cirrhosis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"586213",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Portal hypertension"
]
},
" can be divided into prehepatic, intrahepatic, and posthepatic causes. The most common cause of portal hypertension is cirrhosis, an intrahepatic form. Examples of pre- and posthepatic portal hypertension are portal vein thrombosis and Budd-Chiari syndrome, respectively. Complications of portal hypertension include gastroesophageal varices, ascites, and spontaneous bacterial peritonitis."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gi_s31_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s31_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Management"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fe4dbc",
"children":[
"Management"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"507721",
"children":[
"To care for patients with cirrhosis, select:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a03ca6",
"children":[
"upper endoscopy for all new patients to evaluate for varices"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"39521f",
"children":[
"ultrasonography to diagnose ascites"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ab0f3e",
"children":[
"paracentesis for newly discovered ascites and calculation of the serum-ascites albumin gradient (SAAG) to diagnose the cause of ascites"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a705d7",
"children":[
"paracentesis with ascitic fluid granulocyte count and culture for any change in mental status or clinical condition to diagnose spontaneous bacterial peritonitis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b7adb0",
"children":[
"vaccination of nonimmune patients against ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hepatitis A virus",
"children":[
"HAV"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hepatitis B virus",
"children":[
"HBV"
]
},
" as well as other routine vaccinations"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gi_s31_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s31_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Follow-up Surveillance"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"3af103",
"children":[
"Follow-up Surveillance"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"607def",
"children":[
"Patients with cirrhosis should undergo ultrasonography screening for HCC every 6 months."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"abc8d7",
"children":[
"Although a plasma ammonia level may be helpful in diagnosing suspected cases of hepatic encephalopathy, monitoring serial ammonia values is not useful."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1529c9",
"children":[
"Head CT in patients with hepatic encephalopathy and otherwise normal neurologic examination is not warranted."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"eaf830",
"children":[
"Use IV, not oral, bisphosphonate therapy in patients with esophageal varices."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s31_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gi_s31_inline_t3"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3152c9",
"children":[
"Liver transplantation is the definitive treatment for patients with end-stage or decompensated liver disease."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"43f6ec",
"children":[
"Stop ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"angiotensin-converting enzyme",
"children":[
"ACE"
]
},
" inhibitors, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"angiotensin receptor blocker",
"children":[
"ARB"
]
},
"s,"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
" in patients with ascites."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b74cf4",
"children":[
"Blood transfusion to hemoglobin >7.0 g/dL leads to increased portal pressures and risk of further bleeding."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b9e523",
"children":[
"Antimicrobial prophylaxis should be administered during variceal bleeding even if ascites is absent."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c9ef5e",
"children":[
"Do not select prophylactic protein restriction to prevent hepatic encephalopathy."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c87d4e",
"children":[
"Do not select neomycin to treat hepatic encephalopathy because of the significant adverse effects of this drug."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s31_5",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e5b1b5",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 55-year-old man with alcoholic cirrhosis is admitted to the hospital with fever and abdominal pain. Paracentesis is performed. The ascitic fluid granulocyte count is 650/μL and serum creatinine is 1.6 mg/dL."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"be812d",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose spontaneous bacterial peritonitis. For management, begin empiric IV cefotaxime and albumin. Do not wait for results of Gram stain or cultures before beginning therapy."
]
}
]
}
]
},
